  "text": "From Lemmas 1.1-1.3, we obtain inclusion sets Γ(A) and K(A) by computing n sets Γ i (A) and n(n − ) sets K i,j (A), respectively. It is noted that K(A) is much sharper than Γ(A) [CITATION_1] . Similarly, the exclusion sets ∆(A) and Λ(A) are composed of n(n − ) sets ∆ i,j (A) and n(n − ) sets Λ ij (A), respectively. To reduce computations, Li et al. [CITATION_2] gave an S-type eigenvalue inclusion set by selecting subset S of N, which K S (A) is made up of |S|(n − |S|) sets K i,j (A).",
